ObjectMap<T>
public static enum ObjectMap.PseudoFieldName extends Enum<ObjectMap.PseudoFieldName>
This is the list of pseudo-fields of class ObjectMap that can be accessed from a StringTemplate V4 template. The enumerated fields can be accessed like ordinary public fields from a StringTemplate V4 template. The dot notation is used to do so. Taking the first named value name_ as example, one would write <obj.name_> to access the related pseudo-field.

A detailed discussion of pseudo-fields and the enumeration of these can be found in the class description of ObjectMap.

  • Enum Constant Details

    • name_

      public static final ObjectMap.PseudoFieldName name_
      The name ObjectMap.name_ of the container of data items.

      From a StringTemplate V4 template the object name would be accessed with an expression like <object.name_>.

      Remark:
      Careful, this yields an Identifier object, not a Java String. Rending the name as <object.name_> in a StringTemplate V4 template will evaluate to the name as C identifier. <object.name_.givenName> rather is what you may intend.

    • itemMap

      public static final ObjectMap.PseudoFieldName itemMap
      The map ObjectMap.itemMap of real data items in the container. (Pseudo-fields are not element of this map.)

      From a StringTemplate V4 template the map would be accessed with an expression like <object.itemMap>. The map is sorted in case-sensitive lexical order of key strings (i.e. names of the data items).

    • noItems

    • exists

      Flag ObjectMap.exists, the presence of the container in the data model.

      From a StringTemplate V4 template the flag would be queried with an expression like <if(container.exists)>Can evaluate container contents<endif>.
